@model SupaSpeedGrader.Models.helpModel

@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Help";
    ViewData["state"] = Model.state;
}

<style>
    h3{
        @* This color is Canvas Blue*@
        color: #21314d;
    }
</style>

<div>
    <h3>Home Page</h3>
    <p> The home page allows you to select a quiz, the sectionns grading and the start question. A rubric could also be added here. </p>
</div>
<div>
    <h3>Rubric Page</h3>
    <h5>Limitations of the Rubric Page</h5>
    <p> Rubrics have to match the number of questions in the quiz even if there are multiple choice questions. Rubric names cannot contain spaces. Rubric comments cannot include special characters. There is a cap of 100 questions. Each rubric can have up to 10 criteria and 9 options per criteria, but must be the same size as all other rubrics for the same quiz. If you add a rubric to a question, you are unable to remove it. </p>
    <h5>How to use</h5>
    <p>The page autogenerates depending on input. The number of questions will generate to the number of inputed questions. In addition the rubric is adjustable with dimensions and size. </p>

</div>
<div>
    <h3>Grade Page</h3>
    <h5> The Answer Bar</h5>
    <p>The Answer Bar contains the Question and the student's answers. The responses are identified by the student ID. </p>
    <h5> The Grading Bar</h5>
    <ul>
        <li> Highlight Key Words: Allows tohe user to highlight key phrases in responses</li>
        <li> Jump to: Jumps to a specified student</li>
        <li>Rubric: This contains a clickable rubric that autopopulates grades and comments. </li>
        <li>
            Revert button: Clears the rubric and comments as well as grade
        </li>
        <li> Save button: Saves grade and comment changes </li>
        <li> Save&Next, Save comments and grade and move to the next response </li>
        <li> Clear Button. The clear button clears the comment box. </li>
    </ul>
</div>



